HEADWORD: Amplexicaul
<hw>Am*plex"i*caul</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>amplexus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>amplecti</ets> to encircle, to
embrace + <ets>caulis</ets> stem: cf. F. <ets>amplexicaule</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Clasping or embracing a stem, as the base of some
leaves.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

